Police in Kirinyaga County are looking for a 54-year-old man who allegedly defiled a Class Five pupil at Muthigini village in Gichugu Constituency, Kirinyaga East.  Gichugu police commander Anthony Mbogo said the suspect is a Sunday School teacher at a local church which the minor also attends.  Her parents had told the police that the suspect lured the girl to his house at Muthigini village on Tuesday when she was on an errand to the local maize mill.   Relatives led by her grandmother took the girl to hospital after realising she was having difficulties walking. Mbogo said over 10 cases of defilement have been reported in his area this month.    Who abducted, tortured and murdered Bashir?  Man in trouble for defiling teenage girls in his house   Murder most foul: Shock as man defiles and stabs two teenagers  Man gets 20-year jail sentence for defiling 5-year-old girl   Coffee farmers from Kirinyaga county set to benefit from value-addition machines  Kirinyaga & Narok listed as counties with most opaque budgets after scoring zero points in survey  Kirinyaga woman donates breasts to women who have lost their breasts to cancer By Patrick Vidija | 22 hours ago By Fidelis Kabunyi | 1 day ago By George Njunge | 1 day ago By Lydiah Nyawira | 2 days ago Grab a copy of the latest Standard for only 10 shillings & access the last 10 editions for free